WorkItem.Description:
Would it be possible to incorporate the 110 & 210 transaction sets into the parser? I'm not sure how complicated they are to add, and I understand if it's not on your project road map. However, I would be very grateful if it was.
 
I am looking to write a freight pay system at work and would like to use your application for to translate the EDI files into XML.
 
Thank you for your time,
Chris Story

Comments.Message: Dannie is away for a couple of days but your question will be answered shortly. Please check back! Thanks for your interest in the .Net x-12 parser.

The specifications have been added to changeset 9383.  I do need some test data.  The specifications I used were http://www.pfizer.com/business/edispecs/ap110.pdf and http://www.pgedi.com/images/maps/3_X12%20v4010%20210%20Freight%20Invoice%20_Outbound_.pdf and http://www.pgedi.com/images/maps/2_X12%20v4010%20210%20Freight%20Invoice%20_Inbound_.pdf.

Let me know if there was any other implementation guides that you are trying to follow.  If you can point me to some sample messages, then I can add unit tests and resolve this issue.

Thanks,
Dannie
